Fortnite is set to launch on the Nintendo Switch in the near future, Eurogamer reports. A leaked list of E3 Nintendo titles circulating the Internet listed the Fortnite among numerous titles which are coming to the handheld console. Eurogamer confirmed that this list was accurate, and stated that Switch owners should expect an official announcement soon. There is currently no information available regarding the pricing or release date of Fortnite for the Nintendo Switch. Fortnite recently began rolling out to mobile devices, capitalising on the demand for battle royale titles on mobile platforms, as demonstrated by the popularity of PUBG Mobile.